================================================================================
ALGORITHM ATTRIBUTION
================================================================================

The Binary Equation Path (BEP) algorithm, on which this software is built,
was originally designed and developed by Rich Wagner. The algorithm centers
on the recurrence f(n) = floor(n/2) applied to binary integer
representations, with an implicit most-significant-bit convention and a
configurable byteWidth parameter. BEP and its derived constructs in this
repository — including but not limited to the inBEP codec family,
NibbleContext (orders 2 and 3), ArithmeticContext, DeltaContext,
TextPipelineCtx (BWT+MTF+RePair+RiceBEP), the LZ77/BEP hybrids (Lz77BepV1
through Lz77BepV3), StrideSplitBep, FloatAwareBep, PreseededNibbleContextBep,
the BEP path-capture diagnostics, and the BLEP1 / Gzipb / Xzb / Zipb / Tarb
container wrappers — are the original work of Rich Wagner unless otherwise
noted in the source files themselves.

